{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a33fb12c-d363-43b6-9c27-66fb8ce02fa9","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, **file compilation order matters** — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first in the `.fsproj`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_f1wKlLpcpS31camy4X5zs5","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-4eb895b447b54137ad64dd17b811de6d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-4eb895b447b54137ad64dd17b811de6d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"2413bc2e-8397-4034-9c32-526943ae89ba","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first - opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second - defines `Domain`)\n3. `Program.fs` (listed third - opens both)\n\n`Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs` in the project file. The correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` (defines types)\n\n\n2. `Services.fs` (uses types from Domain)\n3. `Program.fs` (uses both)","outputTokens":465,"requestId":"73D1:14EAB3:15D7C33:1861123:6A051DB2"},"id":"5b108b9e-4d17-4225-8ee7-ea5f823e2e59","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:56:26.731Z","parentId":"0377c7ff-99a0-4e23-a1b1-c5aa0c3215fd"}
